To support developing countries to implement international agreements on climate change, biodiversity, land degradation and harmful chemicals as integral elements of sustainable development. GEF’s other activities include sustainable forest management, international waters and protecting the ozone layer.

This programme provides funding and a mechanism to increase access to academic expertise on FCDO's priorities. It will likely include long-term academic secondments into FCDO and establishing a network of academics that work with the department on medium- and short-term commissions.

The Local Infrastructure Services Programme (LISP) will improve the ability of Nepal’s local and provincial governments to respond to the demands of rural citizens for local infrastructure and it increase the legitimacy and accountability of local government to their citizens with an emphasis on the empowerment of women. It will create green recovery jobs to stimulate the local economy and build climate resilience. LISP will do this by providing technical assistance and performance-based funding for local infrastructure and using government systems.

The Government of Ghana (GoG) is pursuing the diversification of the economy by identifying priority sectors for inclusive and transformational growth and working to attract private sector investment into them. This is intended to spur industrialisation through manufacturing and in-country value-addition. The JET programme is an industrialisation-focused initiative aligned with this objective and the GoG’s vision to move ‘Ghana beyond Aid’. The programme also seeks to strengthen partnerships and increase investment flows between the UK and Ghana and is a catalyst for a new strategic economic development partnership between the two countries.
